    <h1>Resorts Around Mumbai</h1>
    <p class="black">Della Resort in Lonavala, the Machan Resort, Mystica Resort in Lonavala, the Dukes Retreat at Khandala, Cloud 9 Hills Resort, Le farm in Lonavala, Zara Resort in Khandala, The Upper Deck Resort in Lonavala, Shangrila Resort at  Mumbai, Zara’s Resort at Khandala, Monteria Resort at Khalapur, Royal Garden Resort at Mumbai, Pinewood Resort at Mumbai, Le Farm at Lonavala, Leisure Stay in Alibaug Resort and so on. <br>

They are the best way to plan a getaway from a hectic schedule. A really good way to spend some quality time with your friends, family or partner over the duration of your stay, resorts around Mumbai are must explore for everyone who wishes to see the best of this region.<br>

These resorts are sure going to attract you with their features, especially the locations that they are set in, like the twin hill stations of Lonavala and Khandala, and the wine world of Nashik. With a wide variety available in many factors, these resorts are the epitome of the fun time that you are going to have here. They work their hardest to provide you with wild views of the valleys of Sahyadris, or an unending spread of the blue sea.<br>

Escape to the Jashan Farms or the luxurious Radisson Blu Resorts and Spa that will fall within a 100 km from Mumbai city if you wish to not stray far from the city. Resorts in locations like Lonavala, Khandala, Kashid, Nasik and Panchgani, the names whose fame precedes their mention, are equally and sometimes even more mind-boggling. All you need to do is go to distances ranging from 100 to 230 km.</p>
  
